Lucian Galade

"Both of them. Around the same time..."

Player

"I agree. We can't trust the reports."

Narrator

He looked surprised for a moment.

Lucian Galade

"This might bring suspicion on our administration. We must be careful."

Lucian Galade

"But I have to say the death of the Chief Justice isn't particularly bad for us. This is mostly good news."

Player

"No. What are you trying to say?"

Lucian Galade

"In any case, now that the seat of Mr. Hawker is vacant, the Court will be voting on a new Chief Justice."

Lucian Galade

"Mrs. Edmonds and Mr. Garaci seem to be the contenders to become the new chief. However, Mrs. Edmonds doesn't have much chance in my opinion."

Lucian Galade

"I have organized several events around Greater Holsord and Nargis to promote our party and talk about our achievements."

Lucian Galade

"We could go over the details of the new manifesto if you want. I believe you've already made a draft."

Narrator

There was a brief silence.

Lucian Galade

"However, now that there is a vacant position, you must appoint a new Justice. I already compiled a list of candidates for you."

Lucian Galade

"However, now that there is a vacant position, you must appoint a new Justice. I already compiled a list of candidates for you."

Player

"I only want the Old Guard gone."

Player_Italic

I decided not to proceed with a whole reshuffle and picked one name to fill the vacant position.

Pick one person to fill the vacant position.

Narrator

He handed me a list of candidates for the Supreme Court. All of the names on it were people who either supported me or supported my party.

Narrator

The names that stood out to me were Gloria Tory, Ovid Grecer and Didier Meye. Mr. Grecer was an experienced judge and Mr. Meye was loyal to the party.

Lucian Galade

"I have some other news for you."

Lucian Galade

"The Assembly is pushing for Mr. Hawker's impeachment as you asked. They already approved his dismissal today."

Lucian Galade

"But with Mr. Hawker gone, the Court will be voting on a new Chief Justice."

Player

"I'd rather have Garaci take the spot. We have a mutual understanding."

Player

"I only want the Old Guard gone."

Player_Italic

I picked five justices to replace the Old Guard.

Replace the Old Guard.

Player_Italic

I decided to proceed with Lucian's list.

Approve the list for a complete reshuffle.

I picked Gloria Tory.

Pick Gloria Tory.

Pick Gloria Tory.

I picked the most loyal judge from the list, Didier Meye.

Pick the most loyal judge.

Narrator

He handed me a list of candidates for the Supreme Court. All of the names on it were people who either supported me or supported my party.

Narrator

Lucian read through the draft.

Player

"I need someone who can get elected as Chief Justice by the Court."

Player

"I need someone who can get elected as Chief Justice by the Court."

Lucian Galade

"Mr. Grecer is definitely a good choice. He is an expert of Sordish and international law. Also, well-respected by the other judges."

Player

"Do you think they'd elect him as Chief Justice?"

Player

"Do you think they'd elect him as Chief Justice?"

Lucian Galade

"Mr. Meye is definitely a good choice. He would be a great asset to have inside the Supreme Court. I'd vouch for his loyalty."

Player

"Do you think they'd elect her as Chief Justice?"

Player

"Do you think they'd elect him as Chief Justice?"

Lucian Galade

"I'd doubt that the Court would elect him, sir. Mr. Garaci has much more influence."

Narrator

He looked at his watch again.

Lucian Galade

"We will take him to the Court in no time."

Narrator

He leaned closer to me.

Player

"Welcome. Petr. Have a seat."

"Welcome Petr. Have a seat."

Lucian Galade

"Before we end the meeting, I want to congratulate you for opening investigations against Tarquin Soll."

Lucian Galade

"I think we can end the meeting here."

Petr Vectern

"We can enact major laws with your new decree powers. You have enough political capital now."

Petr Vectern

"What are your thoughts, Anton?"

Player

"I have a few ideas myself."

Narrator

I took a look at the documents.

Lucian Galade

"All of them! All three. Gone."

Lucian Galade

"Mr. Kibener was found dead this morning."

Lucian Galade

"I suppose our plans for an alliance with his party are also no longer valid."

Karl Greiser

"Sir I have some unfortunate news. Our attempt on the Chief Justice's life has failed. His dog drank the poison we had prepared for him."

Karl Greiser

"Hawker has increased his security detail and it looks like future attempts will be futile."

Player

"I'll give them whatever they need."
